# Page Component Migration Patterns

## Page Structure
```tsx
// ✅ NativeWind Page Pattern
export function IntroPage() {
  return (
    <ScrollView className="flex-1 bg-background">
      <View className="px-4 py-6">
        <Text className="text-2xl font-bold text-foreground mb-4">
          Page Title
        </Text>
        <View className="space-y-4">
          {/* Page content */}
        </View>
      </View>
    </ScrollView>
  );
}
```

## Interactive Elements
- Migrate Tamagui interactive components to NativeWind equivalents
- Use Pressable/TouchableOpacity with proper className styling
- Implement proper focus and pressed states

## Typography Hierarchy
```tsx
// ✅ Consistent typography classes
<Text className="text-3xl font-bold text-foreground">Heading 1</Text>
<Text className="text-xl font-semibold text-foreground">Heading 2</Text>
<Text className="text-base text-muted-foreground">Body text</Text>
<Text className="text-sm text-muted-foreground">Caption</Text>
```

## Carousel and Animation
- If using react-native-reanimated, ensure compatibility with NativeWind
- Use transform utilities for animations where possible
- Maintain smooth performance during transitions

## Migration Priority Order
1. **Layout structure** - Get the basic page layout working
2. **Typography** - Ensure text hierarchy is correct  
3. **Interactive elements** - Buttons, links, touchable areas
4. **Visual elements** - Images, icons, decorative components
5. **Animations** - Complex transitions and effects